  "texts": [
    "The particle size of FA varies from 1 to over 100 μm, with most particles being smaller than 20 μm.",
    "Additionally, its surface area can range between 200 and 700 m 2 /kg, depending on its chemical composition.",
    "FA is categorized into two types based on its chemical composition: Class F and Class C. Class F FA contains at least 70% combined silicon dioxide (SiO 2), aluminum oxide (Al 2 O 3), and iron oxide (Fe 2 O 3), while Class C contains at least 50% of these components.",
    "These classifications are essential for determining the suitability of FA for different concrete applications, underscoring its critical role in enhancing the performance of concrete structures [3].",
    "Rice husks, the outer coating of rice seeds, are especially notable for their exceptionally high silica content, which can reach up to 85%."
